-- Deutsche Bank Hires Lampard to Head Canada Sales and Trading From Toronto
-- Craig Trudell
-- 2010-07-21T15:51:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/deutsche-bank-hires-jeffrey-mayer-to-run-global-markets-for-north-america.html

          
          
             Deutsche Bank AG , Germanyâ€™s biggest
bank, hired  Scott Lampard  from Bank of America Corp. to manage
sales and trading in Canada.  
 Lampard was head of global markets in Asia and
international capital markets in London at Bank of America,
Frankfurt-based Deutsche Bank said today in a statement. He will
be based in Toronto and report to  Jeffrey Mayer , head of global
markets for North America, and  Paul Jurist , chief officer for
Canada.  
 Deutsche Bank hired Mayer, 51, last week from  UBS AG , where
he was executive chairman of fixed-income, currencies and
commodities and head of complex structured products. Lampard
previously spent 13 years at JPMorgan Chase & Co., Deutsche Bank
said in its statement.  
